user_friendly_variable_name: School food authorities serving local food, count
variable_definition: Number of school food authorities (SFAs) serving local food
source: USDA Farm to School Census
general_comments: The FTS Census has data for each SFA and the geographic identifier they have provided is the ZIP code. To match SFA to a single county, we use a ZIP to County crosswalk. The crosswalk matches the county with the largest percentage of the ZIP population. So, it is not a perfect one-to-one match, but the best we can do with the available data; https://www.unitedstateszipcodes.org/zip-code-database/

user_friendly_variable_name: Racial diversity index
variable_definition: Constructed racial diversity index from 0 (no diversity) to 10 (complete diversity), 2010
source: U.S. Census Bureau, Modified Race Data (2010)
general_comments: A Herfindahl-Hirschman Index (HHI) is computed based on the percentage of the population in each racial category, where a larger HHI represents less diversity. For ease of exposition, we subtract the HHI from 10,000 (no diversity) and standardize the result on a scale from 0 (no diversity) to 10 (complete diversity). Calculations can be found in R Markdown file.
